City Hall will be lit Yellow to support Strive To Be Kind Day.

The Allison Baden-Clay Foundation aims to reduce the incidents of family and domestic violence through education programs in the community, schools and corporates. The Foundation was established following the murder of Allison in 2012, and Strive To Be Kind Day brings about awareness and raises funds for the elimination of domestic abuse and coercive control. It also celebrates Allison&#39;s life as her family and friends share the Strive To Be Kind Day lunch in Brisbane each year. The state is encouraged to wear yellow, buy a sunflower and perform a random act of kindness.

This Light Up is organised by: Allison Baden Clay Foundation&nbsp;
